[Although it seems quite late in the year for EEE, the southern states remain unusually warm, and the recent hurricanes and tropical storms have left standing water in many places that are breeding locations for mosquitoes. Any standing water, whether in catch pots of potted plants or old tires, bird baths, or any other standing water, regardless of size, provides breeding locations and opportunities for mosquitoes. Eliminate the standing water.

As this article mentions, vaccinate your animals, even now. The warm weather in the southern regions still have a large EEE potential. If your animal was vaccinated more than 3 months ago, please consider revaccinating, as the immunity to EEE wanes rather rapidly, lasting only about 3-4 months.

Please remember to use horse-approved mosquito repellent on your animal, and appropriate repellant for yourself. - Mod.TG

